            "answer_text": "Actually it says there are always statements in every formal system that cannot be proved or disproved with founding axioms of that system. (So for that formal system it is unknown if those statements are true or not, so you are not allowed to say \u201ca true statement that can not be proved\u201d). That is why no universe can be consistent and complete. Additionally it says any system can not prove itself being consistent either. The rest is stated perfectly in David Joyce's answer; you\u2019ll always need additional axioms to prove those statements. ",
